<div id="review_674489398" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/674489398" />
    <a title="Nick Iuppa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22429985-nick-iuppa"><img alt="Nick Iuppa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442896406p2/22429985.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/674489398?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nick Iuppa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nick Iuppa" href="/user/show/22429985-nick-iuppa">Nick Iuppa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer674489398" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15748984537309997297">The Hummingbird&apos;s Daughter by Luis Urrea is the true story of a strong-willed, teenage Mexican girl in the 19th century. She was said to have miraculous healing powers, inspired the common people to value their native identity, and in the end helped bring about the Mexican Revolution. Can&apos;t get over it. A poetic page-turner.</span>
  <span id="freeText15748984537309997297" style="display:none">The Hummingbird's Daughter by Luis Urrea is the true story of a strong-willed, teenage Mexican girl in the 19th century. She was said to have miraculous healing powers, inspired the common people to value their native identity, and in the end helped bring about the Mexican Revolution. Can't get over it. A poetic page-turner.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15748984537309997297" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


